projects.title: Real Estate Website
projects.content: My partner and I are developing a full stack real estate management website designed to manage tenants, properties, and maintenance requests. It will also handle payment systems, user privileges, and database management. It is designed for and hired by real estate managers to manage properties.

projects.title: Bug Blog
projects.content: Using vanilla Javascript, HTML, and CSS, with no frameworks or styling guidelines, to fuel my love for insects, I am creating a full stack social media platform for insect photographers. It will utilize user authentication and permissions to allow different types of ratings on posts. Each post will be rated with an audience and user score. Right now, the website is a working shell with an implemented PHP backend.

projects.title: YouTube Title Analyzer
projects.content: I worked with a team of three to develop a frontend-only website that compares the efficiency of two data structures: a Trie and a HashMap to analyze YouTube video titles. Our goal was to visualize and analyze the performance of the two data structures in sorting and analyzing YouTube video titles. We used the YouTube 8M API for the data (utilizing over 100,000 data points at a time). We implemented real-time animation, using Framer-Motion. When a user searches for a YouTube video title, the website will animate the search process for better visualization. The title optimization algorithm was based ono an analysis of YouTube video titles based on metrics like comments, views, and likes to help content creators optimize their titles for better engagement.
